            "draft_value": "* Over $17.4M in NASA Science obligations to NC-4 since FY2023, including $8.7M for Duke University and $6.3M for UNC Chapel Hill to support Roman Telescope development and urban heat research\n* Strategic $9B investment to counter China's rapid expansion in space exploration and ensure the U.S. continues to set international norms for the 21st-century space economy\n* Economic return of $3 for every $1 invested, stabilizing a specialized innovation workforce and providing a critical talent pipeline for North Carolina's technology sector\n* Adherence to National Academies' Decadal Surveys, prioritizing peer-reviewed, high-impact missions that address urgent climate challenges and fundamental scientific discovery",
